subproject.description: The first stage of HPMP which is presented will effectively target reaching the freeze by 2013 and 10% reduction of baseline phase out level by 2015. This HCFC Phase out Management Plan (HPMP) documents the analysis and actions proposed by the government of the Republic of Kyrgyzstan in respect to meeting the obligations assumed under Decision XIX/6 of the Parties to the Montreal Protocol on the accelerated phase of HCFC’s.  It has been prepared by the National Ozone Unit with the support of UNDP acting as implementing agency. The project will be implemented by UNDP as a lead agency and UNEP as a cooperating agency. It is intended to serve as an integral component of the country’s policy and commitment to meet its obligations under the Montreal Protocol.
subproject.title: HCFC PHASE-OUT MANAGEMENT PLAN
